<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Several airlines add U.S.-Aruba flights  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ORANJESTAD, Aruba (AP) - Several airlines plan to add flights
between the United States and Aruba this year, the Dutch Caribbean
island's government announced.
</P>
<P>
   On July 1, Delta Airlines will schedule daily nonstop service
from Atlanta to Aruba and Air Aruba will add a daily flight from
Orlando, Florida, the island's Ministry of Tourism said in a
statement.
</P>
<P>
   US Airways will add a daily flight between Philadelphia and
Aruba in November. And in December, Delta Airlines will have a
daily from New York, while Continental Airlines will begin flying
to Aruba four times a week from Newark, N.J.
</P>
<P>
   The U.S. Customs Service opened an office in April in the
island's recently renovated Queen Beatrix International Airport in
Aruba to allow U.S.-bound air passengers to clear customs before
leaving the island.
</P>
</TEXT>
