<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Second teen dies after car wreck  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - A 15-year-old boy who was critically hurt
when a car traveling at high speed crashed into a tree, killing a
teen-age friend, has died of his injuries.
</P>
<P>
   Richard Karnisky had sustained severe head trauma in the one-car
crash June 15 in the Rochester suburb of Gates. He died at hospital
Thursday night.
</P>
<P>
   His friend, Rudy Profetta, 16, was killed in the wreck.
</P>
<P>
   Another 16-year-old, Christoper Hern, fractured his hip and
sustained cuts and bruises and a lacerated spleen. He was released
from the hospital last week.
</P>
<P>
   Police said Profetta was driving faster than 60 mph and had been
drinking alcohol the night of the crash.
</P>
</TEXT>
