<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Spanish Arrest 21, Seize Cocaine  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MADRID, Spain (AP) -- Spanish Civil Guards with help from the
U.S. Drug Enforcement Agency seized a freighter carrying more than
2 tons of cocaine in the Caribbean, arresting 21 people in the
operation, authorities said Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   The Cape Verde-registered freighter ''Paul'' was intercepted
Wednesday near France's Martinique Island with about 2.2 tons of
cocaine, though police suspect the crew threw part of the smuggled
drug into the sea.
</P>
<P>
   The drug was heading to the Spain's northwestern region of
Galicia with a street value of $194 million, a police statement
said.
</P>
<P>
   Nine people were arrested aboard the ship, while four others
were detained on or near the freighter, EFE state news agency
reported. No nationalities or identities were released.
</P>
<P>
   Another eight people suspected of being part of a
drug-trafficking organization were arrested in different northern
Spanish towns in connection with the bust.
</P>
</TEXT>
