<DOCNO> APW20000624.0093 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-24 17:57 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Whitman outlaws nudity at Cape May beach  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   TRENTON, N.J. (AP) - Nudity is now a no-no along all but one
patch of the Jersey shore.
</P>
<P>
   Gov. Christie Whitman closed a legal loophole that made clothing
optional along a stretch of the Cape May shoreline.
</P>
<P>
   The only exception to the law is the clothing-optional Gunnison
Beach at Gateway National Recreation Area on Sandy Hook, which is
part of the National Park system.
</P>
<P>
   ''New Jersey's beaches are the cleanest, most family-friendly
beaches in North America. We have an obligation to keep them that
way,'' Whitman said.
</P>
<P>
   With her signature, the governor formally approved special
legislation that outlaws nude bathing at Higbee Beach.
</P>
<P>
   A 300-foot section of the beach in Lower Township had been
exempt from state and local laws banning nudity.
</P>
<P>
   About 650 acres of the beach and dune preserve is federal
property, where the local restrictions did not apply.
</P>
<P>
   Area residents have long complained of sexual activity and lewd
behavior by tourists attracted to the nude beach.
</P>
<P>
   Local officials recently pointed to several Internet sites that
apparently promoted the beach and its all-natural option.
</P>
<P>
   ''I signed the legislation to completely ban nude sunbathing
last night, before summer tourism kicks into high gear at the
shore,'' Whitman said in statement released Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   ''There are a million and one appropriate things to do at the
beach. Nude sunbathing and lewd behavior on public property are not
among them,'' the governor said.
</P>
<P>
   New Jersey Department of Fish, Game and Wildlife officials, who
help patrol the beach, have reported arrests for illegal behavior.
</P>
<P>
   But beachgoers complain that new laws should target lewd
behavior, not the nudity.
</P>
<P>
   The law Whitman signed clarified an earlier law that ensured no
one can disrobe on government-owned land. The original law decreed
that a town could forbid nudity on ''state-owned lands within its
borders,'' but did not include federal land.
</P>
<P>
   The revised measure allows towns to prohibit nudity on all land
''under the jurisdiction of the state,'' which includes both state
and federally owned properties.
</P>
<P>
   Higbee Beach is leased to Lower Township, and therefore falls
under the state's jurisdiction. Gateway National Park is supervised
by the National Park Service.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-06-24-00 1757 </TRAILER>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> APW20000624.0094 </DOCNO>
<DOCTYPE> NEWS STORY </DOCTYPE>
<DATE_TIME> 2000-06-24 18:05 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Groom uses 'Net to bring wedding to parents  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   BINGHAMTON, N.Y. (AP) - Dan Abashian would have loved to have
his parents at his wedding Saturday.
</P>
<P>
   But he would rather they be healthy enough to stick around
longer term so when illnesses prevented them from coming to the
wedding, Abashian turned to the Internet to bring the wedding to
them.
</P>
<P>
   He and new bride Nancy Housel arranged for a videographer to
film the wedding then contacted a local business to stream the feed
onto the Internet.
</P>
<P>
   Cables were run in the church and at the local hospital where
Abashian's mother was recovering from cancer surgery. His father,
recovering in Jupiter, Fla., after chest pains and pacemaker
surgery, will watch from there as the couple says, ''I do.''
</P>
<P>
   The ceremony also was broadcast co-workers in Rochester and
family and friends as far away as Germany and Denmark.
</P>
<P>
   Cliff Aerie, pastor at First Congregational Church in
Binghamton, said he has never done an Internet wedding before.
</P>
<P>
   ''When you can use a technology like that to make a difference
in people's lives, it's tremendous,'' he said.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER> AP-ES-06-24-00 1805 </TRAILER>
