<HEADLINE> Coyotes Acquire May From Canucks  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   SCOTTSDALE, Ariz. (AP) -- The Phoenix Coyotes acquired left wing
Brad May Saturday from the Vancouver Canucks for future
considerations.
</P>
<P>
   Coyotes general manager Bobby Smith said May signed a multiyear
contract but would not disclose financial terms.
</P>
<P>
   May, 28, had nine goals, seven assists and 90 penalty minutes in
59 games last season. He was obtained by the Canucks in February
1998 in a trade with Buffalo for Geoff Sanderson.
</P>
<P>
   May was the Sabres' first round draft pick in 1990 and had a
career-high 309 penalty minutes in 69 games as a rookie.
</P>
<P>
   The rugged forward scored a career-best 18 goals in 84 games in
1993-94 and has 1,556 penalty minutes in 571 career NHL games.
</P>
