<HEADLINE> Mercury 67, Sol 44  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   MIAMI (AP) -- Tonya Edwards scored 12 points and Jennifer Gillom
added 10 as the Phoenix Mercury routed the expansion Miami Sol
67-44 on Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Brandy Reed, Bridget Pettis and Lisa Harrison each had eight
points for Phoenix, which has won three straight to improve to 8-3.
</P>
<P>
   Miami (4-8) tied the WNBA record for fewest field goals (14) and
set a team record for lowest field-goal percentage (22.6). The 44
points are the fewest ever allowed by the Mercury.
</P>
<P>
   Milena Flores led the Sol with eight points and eight rebounds.
</P>
<P>
   She hit a 3-pointer with 9.6 seconds left to keep Miami from
tying the WNBA record for fewest points in a game of 41 set by
Sacramento against Detroit on Aug. 11, 1998.
</P>
<P>
   Phoenix led 39-17 at the half, with the Sol tying the franchise
record for fewest points in an opening half.
</P>
<P>
   Miami missed 10 of its first 12 shots, while Phoenix made seven
of its first 13 attempts to take a 17-5 lead. Phoenix shot 60
percent (15-of-25) in the half, while Miami shot 17.9 percent
(5-of-28). Phoenix shot 54.2 percent (26-of-48) overall.
</P>
<P>
   Marlies Askamp, playing against her former team for the first
time, Jameka Jones and Kristen Rasmussen each had seven points for
Miami.
</P>
</TEXT>
