<HEADLINE> Miracle 69, Sting 68  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   ORLANDO, Fla. (AP) -- Taj McWilliams made a layup with 10.1
seconds remaining as Orlando beat Charlotte 69-68 on Saturday night
to take a half-game lead in the WNBA's Eastern Conference.
</P>
<P>
   Charlotte's Andrea Stinson missed a 15-foot jumper with
seven-tenths of a second remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Nykesha Sales led Orlando (7-5) with 22 points and 10 rebounds.
Adrienne Johnson added 13 points and McWilliams had 12.
</P>
<P>
   Stinson, Tiffany Travis and Tracy Reid each had 13 points for
Charlotte (2-10) and Shalonda Enis added 12.
</P>
<P>
   McWilliams gave the Miracle a 67-63 lead with 2:26 left, but
Charlotte countered with Dawn Staley's 3-pointer and Stinson's
basket to take a 68-67 lead.
</P>
<P>
   Reid had a chance to extend Charlotte's lead, but missed two
free throws with 28.4 seconds remaining.
</P>
<P>
   Orlando has beaten the Sting three times this season by a
combined seven points. The Miracle had 10 blocked shots, three by
rookie center Cintia Dos Santos.
</P>
</TEXT>
