<HEADLINE> Queenie Belle Wins Princess Stakes  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   INGLEWOOD, Calif. (AP) -- Favorite Queenie Belle captured the
$150,000 Princess Stakes by two lengths Saturday at Hollywood Park.
</P>
<P>
   Ridden by Brice Blanc, Queenie Belle overtook pacesetter Annie
Lil at the top of the stretch and overpowered both Cash Run and
Saudi Poetry for her first stakes victory.
</P>
<P>
   The daughter of Bertrando covered the 1 1-16 miles in 1:43 2-5
and paid $6.40, $3.40 and $2.40; and the $90,000 winners share
raised her career earnings to $290,620.
</P>
<P>
   Saudi Poetry, ridden by Corey Nakatani, overtook Cash Run down
the stretch and paid $3.60 and $2.60. Cash Run paid $2.60 to show.
</P>
