<HEADLINE> Richmond 6, Rochester 3  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
	   ROCHESTER, N.Y. (AP) - Tyrone Pendergrass drove in three runs to
lead the Richmond Braves to a 6-3 victory over the Rochester Red
Wings in International League baseball Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   Pendergrass gave Richmond a one-run lead three times. After
leadoff batter George Lombard tripled in the first and third
innings, Pendergrass drove him in - first with a sacrifice fly,
then with a ground out. His fifth-inning single gave the Braves a
3-2 lead they never lost.
</P>
<P>
   Richmond added three runs in the sixth inning against losing
pitcher Brian Shouse (1-4). Pascual Matos doubled for one run, and
Chris Petersen doubled home two more.
</P>
<P>
   Rochester's Jose Herrera scored two runs and drove in two. He
tripled and scored on a ground out in the first inning, hit his
third home run this season in the third and singled home the final
run in the ninth.
</P>
<P>
   Winning pitcher Dan Smith (3-4) worked two scoreless innings in
relief as Richmond (23-49) won its second consecutive game. The Red
Wings fell to 34-37.
</P>
</TEXT>
