<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Arizona Activates 1B Durazo  </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
   PHOENIX (AP) -- The Arizona Diamondbacks activated first baseman
Erubiel Durazo from the 15-day disabled list Saturday and
designated outfielder Bernard Gilkey for assignment.
</P>
<P>
   The Diamondbacks went into Saturday night's game with the
Colorado Rockies 7-11 in their last 18 -- a stretch in which they
scored more than four runs just four times.
</P>
<P>
   Durazo, 25, who hit over .400 with two minor league teams before
he was called up last year, has hit .287 in 44 games this season.
He had six homers and 24 RBIs before he went on the DL on May 30.
</P>
<P>
   He had surgery June 1 to repair torn cartilage in his right
wrist.
</P>
<P>
   During a rugged rehabilitation this week, Durazo played in a
doubleheader for Triple-A Tucson and an extended spring game in an
18-hour span. He would have been activated Friday night, but the
Rockies used left-hander Brian Bohanon, and Arizona manager Buck
Showalter wanted him to get his first start against right-hander
Masato Yoshii, who started Saturday night.
</P>
<P>
   If Gilkey, hitting .110 in 38 games, clears waivers the team
will owe him nearly $3.5 million of his $5.25 million contract.
</P>
</TEXT>
